%N A395281 Decimal expansion of tan(3 * Pi / 13).
%C A395281 This constant is a special case of a general identity. For any odd integer k >= 3, define the infinite product P(k) = Product_{m>=0} f((2*m+1)*k), where:
%C A395281   f(n) = (n-1)/(n+1) if n == 1 (mod 4);
%C A395281   f(n) = (n+1)/(n-1) if n == 3 (mod 4).
%C A395281 This product converges to tan(j*Pi/k), where j = floor((k+1)/4).
%C A395281 The sequence of numerators j for k = 3, 5, 7, 9, 11, 13, ... is 1, 1, 2, 2, 3, 3, ... (A004526).
%C A395281 Equivalently, the product can be written using the Dirichlet character modulo 4 (A010892) as:
%C A395281   P(k) = Product_{m>=0} (( (2*m+1)*k - 1 ) / ( (2*m+1)*k + 1 ))^(-chi4((2*m+1)*k));
%C A395281 For k = 13, j = floor(14/4) = 3, so the product converges to tan(3*Pi/13).
%C A395281 Also, a root of the polynomial x^12 - 78*x^10 + 715*x^8 - 1716*x^6 + 1287*x^4 - 286*x^2 + 13.
%H A395281 <a href="/index/Tra#tan">Index to sequences related to decimal expansions of tan(x)</a>
%H A395281 <a href="/index/Al#algebraic_12">Index entries for algebraic numbers, degree 12</a>
%F A395281 Equals tan(3*Pi/13).
%F A395281 Equals Sum_{n>=1} -(((-4)^n * (4^n - 1) * B_{2*n} * (3/13)^(2*n-1)) / (2*n)! ) * Pi^(2*n-1).
%F A395281 Equals Product_{m>=0} f((2*m+1)*13), where f(n) = (n-1)/(n+1) if n == 1 (mod 4) and f(n) = (n+1)/(n-1) if n == 3 (mod 4).
%e A395281 0.885922693643422280142121178600396087556...
%t A395281 RealDigits[Tan[3*Pi/13], 10, 120][[1]] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Apr 18 2026 *)
%o A395281 (PARI) print(tan(3*Pi/13));
